<section xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:lang="en-US" xml:id="geogebra-parabola-standard-form-one">
  <title>Determine the Vertex of a Parabola Given in Standard Form - Part I</title>

  <figure xml:id="geogebra-parabola-standard-form-one-geogebra">
    <caption>Determine the vertex of the parabola that arises from the given equation.  Then drag the vertex of the parabola to the point that matches that vertex. A message will appear when you are correct.</caption>
    <interactive platform="geogebra" width="100%" aspect="9:5">
      <slate surface="geogebra" aspect="9:5" source="geogebra/paraola-vertex-a-1.ggb">
        setPerspective("G");
        setGridVisible(1);         
        setAxisLabels(1,"x","y","z");
      </slate>
    </interactive>
  </figure>

</section>
